                <note rend="inline" type="source">653.116/39: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Portugal</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Andrews</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-04-13T14:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 13, 1928—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>10. Your 15, April 10, 7 p.m. If subsidy of one and one-half escudos per ton upon
                    coal imported in Portuguese vessels is payable to Portuguese shipowners,
                    Department perceives no ground for representations. Such a measure must be
                    accepted as direct subsidy. On the other hand, if such payments are made to
                    importers who patronize national vessels for the purpose of giving the latter an
                    advantage over competing foreign vessels in obtaining cargo, you should make
                    informal representations, pointing out that abandonment of discriminating import
                    duties in favor of national vessels will be rendered illusory if measures so
                    similar in their effects are substituted.</p>
                <p>Keep Department closely advised.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
